<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="48" pageId="4" pageNumber="47" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1778,2028]" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,313,1890,1916]" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">Remarks</emphasis>
. The description of 
<taxonomicName authority="in Stimpson (1858)" authorityName="in Stimpson" authorityYear="1858" box="[561,1080,1890,1916]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dotillidae" genus="Scopimera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="4" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuberculata">
<emphasis box="[561,837,1890,1915]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">Scopimera tuberculata</emphasis>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Stimpson, W." box="[877,1080,1890,1916]" journalOrPublisher="Pars 5. Proceedings of the Academia of Natural Science, Philadelphia" pageId="4" pageNumber="47" pagination="93 - 110" part="10" refString="Stimpson, W. (1858) Crustacea Ocypodoidea. Prodromus descriptionis animalium evertebratorum, quae in Expeditione ad Oceanum Pacificum Septentrionalem a Republica Federata missa, Cadwaladaro Ringgold et Johanne Rodgers ducibus, observavit et descripsit, Pars 5. Proceedings of the Academia of Natural Science, Philadelphia, 10, 93 - 110." title="Crustacea Ocypodoidea. Prodromus descriptionis animalium evertebratorum, quae in Expeditione ad Oceanum Pacificum Septentrionalem a Republica Federata missa, Cadwaladaro Ringgold et Johanne Rodgers ducibus, observavit et descripsit" type="journal article" year="1858">Stimpson (1858)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was too brief and it does not provide diagnostic character to differentiate 
<taxonomicName box="[680,845,1928,1953]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dotillidae" genus="Scopimera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="4" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuberculata">
<emphasis box="[680,845,1928,1953]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">S. tuberculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from most of other known species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1302,1428,1928,1953]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dotillidae" genus="Scopimera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="4" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1302,1428,1928,1953]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">Scopimera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Stimpson, W." box="[151,356,1965,1991]" journalOrPublisher="Smithsonian Miscellaneous Collections" pageId="4" pageNumber="47" pagination="1 - 240" part="49" refString="Stimpson, W. (1907) Report on the Crustacea (Brachyura and Anomura) collected by the North Pacific Exploring Expedition, 1853 - 1856. Smithsonian Miscellaneous Collections, 49 (1717), 1 - 240." title="Report on the Crustacea (Brachyura and Anomura) collected by the North Pacific Exploring Expedition, 1853 - 1856" type="journal article" year="1907">Stimpson (1907)</bibRefCitation>
later commented that 
<taxonomicName box="[633,912,1965,1990]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dotillidae" genus="Scopimera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="4" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuberculata">
<emphasis box="[633,912,1965,1990]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">Scopimera tuberculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
“differs from De Haan’s 
<taxonomicName box="[1229,1358,1965,1990]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dotillidae" genus="Scopimera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="4" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="globosa">
<emphasis box="[1229,1358,1965,1990]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">S. globosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the character of the upper surface of the carapax and in the obliquity of the meros-joint in the outer maxillipeds”.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,152,1111]" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">
<bibRefCitation author="Koelbel, K." box="[151,340,152,178]" journalOrPublisher="Wissenschaftliche Ergebnisse der Reise des Grafen Bela Szechenyi in Ostasien" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" pagination="709 - 718" part="2" refString="Koelbel, K. (1897) Beschreibung der Krebse. Wissenschaftliche Ergebnisse der Reise des Grafen Bela Szechenyi in Ostasien, 2, 709 - 718." title="Beschreibung der Krebse" type="journal article" year="1897">Koelbel (1897)</bibRefCitation>
, using specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[631,778,152,178]" name="Hong Kong" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">Hong Kong</collectingCountry>
, suggested 
<taxonomicName box="[920,1091,152,177]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dotillidae" genus="Scopimera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuberculata">
<emphasis box="[920,1091,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">S. tuberculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was a junior synonym as 
<taxonomicName class="Malacostraca" family="Dotillidae" genus="Scopimera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="globosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">S. globosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Tesch, J. J." box="[266,429,189,215]" journalOrPublisher="Grapsidae and Gecarcinidae. Sigoba Expeditie Monographie" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" pagination="1 - 148" part="39" refString="Tesch, J. J. (1918) The Brachyura of the Sigoba Expedition. Hymenosomidae, Ocypodidae, Grapsidae and Gecarcinidae. Sigoba Expeditie Monographie, 39 c, 1 - 148." title="The Brachyura of the Sigoba Expedition. Hymenosomidae, Ocypodidae" type="journal article" year="1918">Tesch (1918)</bibRefCitation>
examined De Haan’s 
<typeStatus box="[707,760,189,215]" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">type</typeStatus>
in Leiden Museum and added to the description of 
<taxonomicName class="Malacostraca" family="Dotillidae" genus="Scopimera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="globosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">S. globosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, agreeing with 
<bibRefCitation author="Koelbel, K." box="[439,624,226,252]" journalOrPublisher="Wissenschaftliche Ergebnisse der Reise des Grafen Bela Szechenyi in Ostasien" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" pagination="709 - 718" part="2" refString="Koelbel, K. (1897) Beschreibung der Krebse. Wissenschaftliche Ergebnisse der Reise des Grafen Bela Szechenyi in Ostasien, 2, 709 - 718." title="Beschreibung der Krebse" type="journal article" year="1897">Koelbel (1897)</bibRefCitation>
that Stimpson’s descriptions on 
<taxonomicName box="[1024,1194,226,251]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dotillidae" genus="Scopimera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuberculata">
<emphasis box="[1024,1194,226,251]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">S. tuberculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
fell well within the intra-specific variation of 
<taxonomicName box="[456,578,264,289]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dotillidae" genus="Scopimera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="globosa">
<emphasis box="[456,578,264,289]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">S. globosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This view has been supported by a number of authors (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Parisi, B." box="[1295,1431,264,290]" journalOrPublisher="Atti della Societa Italiana de Scienze Naturali" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" pagination="5 - 42" part="57" refString="Parisi, B. (1918) I Decapodi giapponesi del Museo di Milano. VI. Catometopa e Paguridea. Atti della Societa Italiana de Scienze Naturali, 57, 5 - 42." title="I Decapodi giapponesi del Museo di Milano. VI. Catometopa e Paguridea" type="journal article" year="1918">Parisi 1918</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Kemp, S." box="[151,293,301,327]" journalOrPublisher="Records of the Indian Museum" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" pagination="48" part="16" refString="Kemp, S. (1919) Notes on Crustacea Decapoda in the Indian Museum. XII. Scopimerinae. Records of the Indian Museum, 16, 305 - 3 48." title="Notes on Crustacea Decapoda in the Indian Museum. XII. Scopimerinae" type="journal article" year="1919">Kemp 1919</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Sakai, T." box="[306,440,301,327]" journalOrPublisher="Tokyo, pp. 365 - 741 + pls" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" pagination="42 - 111" refString="Sakai, T. (1939) Studies on the Crabs of Japan. IV. Brachygnatha, Brachyrhyncha. Yokendo, Tokyo, pp. 365 - 741 + pls. 42 - 111." title="Studies on the Crabs of Japan. IV. Brachygnatha, Brachyrhyncha. Yokendo" type="book chapter" year="1939">Sakai 1939</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Sakai, T." bookContentInfo="206 pp." box="[453,515,301,327]" journalOrPublisher="Tokyo" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" refString="Sakai, T. (1965) The Crabs of Sagami Bay. Maruzen, Tokyo, 206 pp. + 100 pls .." title="The Crabs of Sagami Bay. Maruzen" type="book" year="1965">1965</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Sakai, T." bookContentInfo="773 pp" box="[527,589,301,327]" journalOrPublisher="Kodansha, Tokyo" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" refString="Sakai, T. (1976) Crabs of Japan and the Adjacent Seas. Kodansha, Tokyo, 773 pp + 251 pls." title="Crabs of Japan and the Adjacent Seas" type="book" year="1976">1976</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Ng, P. K. L., Wang, C. - H., Ho, P. - H. &amp; Shih, H. - T" box="[602,775,301,327]" journalOrPublisher="National Taiwan Museum Special Publication Series" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" pagination="1 - 86" part="11" refString="Ng, P. K. L., Wang, C. - H., Ho, P. - H. &amp; Shih, H. - T. (2001) An annotated checklist of brachyuran crabs from Taiwan (Crustacea: Decapoda). National Taiwan Museum Special Publication Series, 11, 1 - 86." title="An annotated checklist of brachyuran crabs from Taiwan (Crustacea: Decapoda)" type="journal article" year="2001">
Ng 
<emphasis box="[646,705,301,326]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">et al.</emphasis>
2001
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ng, P. K. L., Guinot, D. &amp; Davie, P. J. F." box="[788,852,301,327]" journalOrPublisher="The Raffles Bulletin of Zoology Supplement" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" pagination="1 - 286" part="17" refString="Ng, P. K. L., Guinot, D. &amp; Davie, P. J. F. (2008) Systema Brachyurorum: Part I. An annotated checklist of the extant brachyuran crabs of the world. The Raffles Bulletin of Zoology Supplement, 17, 1 - 286." title="Systema Brachyurorum: Part I. An annotated checklist of the extant brachyuran crabs of the world" type="journal article" year="2008">2008</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Sakai, T." box="[872,1023,301,327]" journalOrPublisher="Tokyo, pp. 365 - 741 + pls" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" pagination="42 - 111" refString="Sakai, T. (1939) Studies on the Crabs of Japan. IV. Brachygnatha, Brachyrhyncha. Yokendo, Tokyo, pp. 365 - 741 + pls. 42 - 111." title="Studies on the Crabs of Japan. IV. Brachygnatha, Brachyrhyncha. Yokendo" type="book chapter" year="1939">Sakai (1939)</bibRefCitation>
further stated that 
<taxonomicName box="[1248,1371,301,326]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dotillidae" genus="Scopimera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="globosa">
<emphasis box="[1248,1371,301,326]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">S. globosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were found in numerous locations of 
<collectingCountry box="[528,595,338,364]" name="Japan" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">Japan</collectingCountry>
and the variation observed only involved one species. On the contrary, unlike his previous report (
<bibRefCitation author="Shen, C. - J." box="[487,624,376,402]" journalOrPublisher="Zoologia Sinica, Series A" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" pagination="1 - 300" part="9" refString="Shen, C. - J. (1932) The brachyuran Crustacea of North China. Zoologia Sinica, Series A, 9, 1 - 300." title="The brachyuran Crustacea of North China" type="journal article" year="1932">Shen 1932</bibRefCitation>
), 
<bibRefCitation author="Shen, C. - J." box="[647,799,376,402]" journalOrPublisher="The Chinese Journal of Zoology" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" pagination="19 - 40" part="1" refString="Shen, C. - J. (1935) On some new and rare crabs of the families Pinnotheridae, Grapsidae and Ocypopidae from China. The Chinese Journal of Zoology, 1, 19 - 40." title="On some new and rare crabs of the families Pinnotheridae, Grapsidae and Ocypopidae from China" type="journal article" year="1935">Shen (1935)</bibRefCitation>
argued for the presence of 
<taxonomicName box="[1140,1313,376,401]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dotillidae" genus="Scopimera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuberculata">
<emphasis box="[1140,1313,376,401]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">S. tuberculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
along the Chinese coasts, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Dai, A. - Y. &amp; Yang, S. - L." bookContentInfo="682 pp." box="[387,611,413,439]" journalOrPublisher="Beijing" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" refString="Dai, A. - Y. &amp; Yang, S. - L. (1991) Crabs of the China Seas. China Ocean Press, Beijing, 682 pp." title="Crabs of the China Seas. China Ocean Press" type="book" year="1991">Dai &amp; Yang (1991)</bibRefCitation>
illustrated the G1 of the species. In the present study, we show that the old records of 
<taxonomicName box="[325,492,450,475]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dotillidae" genus="Scopimera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuberculata">
<emphasis box="[325,492,450,475]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">S. tuberculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from South 
<collectingCountry box="[642,713,450,476]" name="China" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">China</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[772,858,450,476]" name="Taiwan" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
should be referred to 
<taxonomicName box="[1124,1282,450,475]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dotillidae" genus="Scopimera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intermedia">
<emphasis box="[1124,1282,450,475]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">S. intermedia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
instead. Our morphological and molecular analyses support the original identification by 
<bibRefCitation author="Tweedie, M. W. F." box="[1095,1292,488,514]" journalOrPublisher="Sarawak Museum Journal" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" pagination="328 - 369" part="5" refString="Tweedie, M. W. F. (1950) Grapsoid crabs from Labuan and Sarawak. Sarawak Museum Journal, 5, 328 - 369." title="Grapsoid crabs from Labuan and Sarawak" type="journal article" year="1950">Tweedie (1950)</bibRefCitation>
. Interesting enough specimens of “ 
<taxonomicName authority="in Shen (1935)" authorityName="in Shen" authorityYear="1935" box="[425,793,525,551]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dotillidae" genus="Scopimera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuberculata">
<emphasis box="[425,592,525,550]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">S. tuberculata</emphasis>
” in 
<bibRefCitation author="Shen, C. - J." box="[645,793,525,551]" journalOrPublisher="The Chinese Journal of Zoology" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" pagination="19 - 40" part="1" refString="Shen, C. - J. (1935) On some new and rare crabs of the families Pinnotheridae, Grapsidae and Ocypopidae from China. The Chinese Journal of Zoology, 1, 19 - 40." title="On some new and rare crabs of the families Pinnotheridae, Grapsidae and Ocypopidae from China" type="journal article" year="1935">Shen (1935)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
also included material from North 
<collectingCountry box="[1218,1289,525,551]" name="China" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">China</collectingCountry>
(nine males from Bohai Bay (= Peichihli Bay), also see 
<bibRefCitation author="Shen, C. - J." box="[663,802,562,588]" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the Institute of Zoology, National Academy of Peiping" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" pagination="277 - 314" part="3" refString="Shen, C. - J. (1937 a) Second addition to the fauna of brachyuran Crustacea of North China, with a check list of the species recorded in this particular region. Contributions from the Institute of Zoology, National Academy of Peiping, 3 (6), 277 - 314." title="Second addition to the fauna of brachyuran Crustacea of North China, with a check list of the species recorded in this particular region" type="journal article" year="1937" yearSuffix="a">Shen 1937a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Shen, C. - J." box="[815,833,562,588]" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the Fan Memorial Institute of Biology (Zoology), 7" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" pagination="167 - 185" part="5" refString="Shen, C. - J. (1937 b) On some account of the crabs of North China. Bulletin of the Fan Memorial Institute of Biology (Zoology), 7 (5), 167 - 185." title="On some account of the crabs of North China" type="journal article" year="1937" yearSuffix="b">b</bibRefCitation>
). However, without further discussion, 
<bibRefCitation author="Dai, A. - Y. &amp; Yang, S. - L." bookContentInfo="682 pp." journalOrPublisher="Beijing" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" refString="Dai, A. - Y. &amp; Yang, S. - L. (1991) Crabs of the China Seas. China Ocean Press, Beijing, 682 pp." title="Crabs of the China Seas. China Ocean Press" type="book" year="1991">Dai &amp; Yang (1991)</bibRefCitation>
excluded the North 
<collectingCountry box="[466,536,600,626]" name="China" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">China</collectingCountry>
record, restricting the distribution of the species to only 
<collectingRegion box="[1195,1332,600,626]" country="China" name="Guangdong" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">Guangdong</collectingRegion>
in South 
<collectingCountry box="[151,227,637,663]" name="China" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">China</collectingCountry>
. The presence of “ 
<taxonomicName box="[455,624,637,662]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dotillidae" genus="Scopimera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuberculata">
<emphasis box="[455,624,637,662]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">S. tuberculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” in North 
<collectingCountry box="[757,832,637,663]" name="China" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">China</collectingCountry>
, as well as the northern distributional limit of the species remains unclear. The record of “ 
<taxonomicName box="[633,800,674,699]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dotillidae" genus="Scopimera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuberculata">
<emphasis box="[633,800,674,699]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">S. tuberculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” from Pam River, 
<collectingCountry box="[1028,1132,674,700]" name="Vietnam" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
, by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kosuge, T. &amp; Wada, K. &amp; Trong, P. D." box="[1182,1431,674,700]" editor="Anh, P. N." journalOrPublisher="Hanoi" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" pagination="178 - 184" refString="Kosuge, T., Wada, K. &amp; Trong, P. D. (1997) Crab distribution in the Cam River estuary, Haiphong, northern Vietnam. In: Anh, P. N., Brands, J. T. &amp; Hong, P. N. (Eds.), National Workshop on the Relationship Between Mangrove Rehabilitation and Coastal Aquaculture in Vietnam. Cres &amp; Actmang, Hanoi, pp. 178 - 184." title="Crab distribution in the Cam River estuary, Haiphong, northern Vietnam" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="National Workshop on the Relationship Between Mangrove Rehabilitation and Coastal Aquaculture in Vietnam. Cres &amp; Actmang" year="1997">
Kosuge 
<emphasis box="[1281,1341,674,699]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">et al.</emphasis>
(1997)
</bibRefCitation>
, are likely to be 
<taxonomicName box="[340,500,712,737]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dotillidae" genus="Scopimera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intermedia">
<emphasis box="[340,500,712,737]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">S. intermedia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as well on the basis of the geographical distribution. The 
<typeStatus box="[1200,1252,712,738]" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">type</typeStatus>
specimen of 
<taxonomicName class="Malacostraca" family="Dotillidae" genus="Scopimera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuberculata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">S. tuberculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was lost in the great Great Chicago Fire in 1871 (
<bibRefCitation author="Stimpson, W." box="[875,1057,749,775]" journalOrPublisher="Smithsonian Miscellaneous Collections" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" pagination="1 - 240" part="49" refString="Stimpson, W. (1907) Report on the Crustacea (Brachyura and Anomura) collected by the North Pacific Exploring Expedition, 1853 - 1856. Smithsonian Miscellaneous Collections, 49 (1717), 1 - 240." title="Report on the Crustacea (Brachyura and Anomura) collected by the North Pacific Exploring Expedition, 1853 - 1856" type="journal article" year="1907">Stimpson 1907</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Evans, A. C." box="[1069,1211,749,775]" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Natural History" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" pagination="399 - 411" part="1" refString="Evans, A. C. (1967) Syntypes of Decapoda described by William Stimpson and James Dana in the collections of the British Museum (Natural History). Journal of Natural History, 1, 399 - 411." title="Syntypes of Decapoda described by William Stimpson and James Dana in the collections of the British Museum (Natural History)" type="journal article" year="1967">Evans 1967</bibRefCitation>
; Vasile 
<emphasis box="[1302,1354,749,774]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">et al</emphasis>
. 2005; 
<bibRefCitation author="Manning, R. B. &amp; Reed, K. J." box="[151,432,786,812]" journalOrPublisher="The Raffles Bulletin of Zoology 54" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" pagination="283 - 293" part="1859" refString="Manning, R. B. &amp; Reed, K. J. (2006) Decapod crustaceans deposited in the Zoological Museum of Copenhagen by William Stimpson in 1859. The Raffles Bulletin of Zoology 54, 283 - 293." title="Decapod crustaceans deposited in the Zoological Museum of Copenhagen by William Stimpson in" type="journal article" year="2006">Manning &amp; Reed 2006</bibRefCitation>
) thus no direct comparison can be made possible. A visit to the 
<typeStatus box="[1219,1271,786,812]" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">type</typeStatus>
locality of 
<taxonomicName class="Malacostraca" family="Dotillidae" genus="Scopimera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuberculata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">S. tuberculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, “Simoda”, by the second author in 2007 failed to collect any specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[1176,1301,824,849]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dotillidae" genus="Scopimera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1176,1301,824,849]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">Scopimera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The entire area around Port Shimoda has been urbanized and the natural beaches and sand flats have long been developed and lost. To eliminate further taxonomic confusion, we now designate a male specimen of 
<taxonomicName box="[151,392,936,961]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dotillidae" genus="Scopimera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="globosa">
<emphasis box="[151,392,936,961]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">Scopimera globosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
collected from nearby Kii Peninsula in 
<collectingCountry box="[898,969,936,962]" name="Japan" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">Japan</collectingCountry>
(CSM-ZC 4195), deposited in 
<collectingRegion box="[1363,1437,936,962]" country="Japan" name="Chiba" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">Chiba</collectingRegion>
Museum, as the 
<typeStatus box="[350,445,973,999]" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">neotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Stimpson, 1858" authorityName="Stimpson" authorityYear="1858" box="[487,959,973,999]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dotillidae" genus="Scopimera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuberculata">
<emphasis box="[487,762,973,998]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">Scopimera tuberculata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Stimpson, W." box="[770,959,973,999]" journalOrPublisher="Pars 5. Proceedings of the Academia of Natural Science, Philadelphia" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" pagination="93 - 110" part="10" refString="Stimpson, W. (1858) Crustacea Ocypodoidea. Prodromus descriptionis animalium evertebratorum, quae in Expeditione ad Oceanum Pacificum Septentrionalem a Republica Federata missa, Cadwaladaro Ringgold et Johanne Rodgers ducibus, observavit et descripsit, Pars 5. Proceedings of the Academia of Natural Science, Philadelphia, 10, 93 - 110." title="Crustacea Ocypodoidea. Prodromus descriptionis animalium evertebratorum, quae in Expeditione ad Oceanum Pacificum Septentrionalem a Republica Federata missa, Cadwaladaro Ringgold et Johanne Rodgers ducibus, observavit et descripsit" type="journal article" year="1858">Stimpson, 1858</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[976,1052,973,999]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,257,1519,1543]" captionTargetBox="[171,1403,1002,1466]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,903,1498]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Dorsal view of the neotype of Scopimera tuberculata Stimpson, 1858. A male (cw 9.9 mm, cl 7.6 mm) (CBM-ZC 4195) deposited in Natural History Museum and Institute, Chiba, Japan." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205334/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). This will settle the taxonomic confusion of related species found in the associated region once and for all and contribute to stability. Through this action, 
<taxonomicName authority="Stimpson, 1858" authorityName="Stimpson" authorityYear="1858" box="[298,784,1048,1074]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dotillidae" genus="Scopimera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuberculata">
<emphasis box="[298,580,1048,1073]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">Scopimera tuberculata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Stimpson, W." box="[589,784,1048,1074]" journalOrPublisher="Pars 5. Proceedings of the Academia of Natural Science, Philadelphia" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" pagination="93 - 110" part="10" refString="Stimpson, W. (1858) Crustacea Ocypodoidea. Prodromus descriptionis animalium evertebratorum, quae in Expeditione ad Oceanum Pacificum Septentrionalem a Republica Federata missa, Cadwaladaro Ringgold et Johanne Rodgers ducibus, observavit et descripsit, Pars 5. Proceedings of the Academia of Natural Science, Philadelphia, 10, 93 - 110." title="Crustacea Ocypodoidea. Prodromus descriptionis animalium evertebratorum, quae in Expeditione ad Oceanum Pacificum Septentrionalem a Republica Federata missa, Cadwaladaro Ringgold et Johanne Rodgers ducibus, observavit et descripsit" type="journal article" year="1858">Stimpson, 1858</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
becomes a subjective junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="De Haan, 1835" authorityName="De Haan" authorityYear="1835" class="Malacostraca" family="Dotillidae" genus="Scopimera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="globosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">Scopimera globosa</emphasis>
De Haan, 1835
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
